At least 30 people reportedly burnt to death in an auto crash along the Zaria-Kano highway in Kaduna state on Thursday. According to reports, the accident involved two 18-seater Toyota buses and a Volkswagen Golf. The Assistant Corps Commander of the Federal Road Safety Corps, Zaria Zone, Abdulrahman Husaini who confirmed the incident said the accident which happened at about 5 pm on Thursday at Hawan Mai Mashi community in Makarfi Local Government Area of Kaduna was caused by a speed violation. He revealed that three vehicles collided on the spot in an attempt by one of the vehicles trying to overtake the other. Most of the passengers according to the personnel were trapped inside the vehicles and got burnt severely, leading to their death.A witness who spoke with Channels TV said the victims had no way to escape from the vehicles. Speaking further, Hussaini said that some injured passengers were rushed to the Ahmadu Bello University Teaching Hospital Shika for urgent medical treatment, while the remains of those that died were evacuated and deposited at the hospital mortuary.